HEADWORD: Lotophagi
<hw>Lo*toph"a*gi</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[L., fr.
Gr. <?/; <?/ the lotus + <?/ to eat.]</ety> <fld>(Class. Myth.)</fld>
<def>A people visited by Ulysses in his wanderings. They subsisted on
the lotus. See <er>Lotus</er> <sd>(b)</sd>, and
<er>Lotus-eater</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
